<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="244" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,589,908,934]" box="[151,589,908,934]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,589,908,934]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,589,908,934]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">
Subfamily 
<taxonomicName authority="Wrigley, 1927" authorityName="Wrigley" authorityYear="1927" box="[287,589,908,934]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Fusininae">
Fusininae 
<bibRefCitation author="Wrigley, A. G." box="[416,589,908,934]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" pagination="216 - 249" refId="ref31963" refString="Wrigley, A. G. (1927) Notes on English Eocene Mollusca, with descriptions of new species. II. The Fusinidae. Proceedings of the Malacological Society of London, 17 (5 - 6), 216 - 249, pls. 33 - 35." type="journal article" year="1927">Wrigley, 1927</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,978,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">
Until recently the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyons &amp; Snyder, 2019" authorityName="Lyons &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2019" box="[432,521,980,1003]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" sensu="lato" status="s.l.">
<emphasis box="[432,521,980,1003]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Fusinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[529,561,978,1003]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[529,554,978,1003]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">s.l</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
was used as a catch-all category to contain several hundred living and fossil species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wrigley" authorityYear="1927" box="[271,384,1014,1039]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Fusininae">Fusininae</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Vermeij, G. J. &amp; Snyder, M. A." box="[551,843,1014,1039]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" pagination="57 - 82" refId="ref31810" refString="Vermeij, G. J. &amp; Snyder, M. A. (2018) Proposed genus-level classification of large species of Fusininae (Gastropoda, Fasciolariidae). Basteria, 82 (4 - 6), 57 - 82." type="journal article" year="2018">Vermeij &amp; Snyder (2018)</bibRefCitation>
, 13 new genera have been introduced between 
<date pageId="5" pageNumber="244" value="2003" valueMax="2018">2003 and 2018</date>
to accommodate many of the more atypical species previously placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lyons &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2019" box="[1123,1212,1052,1075]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1123,1212,1052,1075]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Fusinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and most recently 
<bibRefCitation author="Vermeij, G. J. &amp; Snyder, M. A." box="[151,446,1086,1111]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" pagination="57 - 82" refId="ref31810" refString="Vermeij, G. J. &amp; Snyder, M. A. (2018) Proposed genus-level classification of large species of Fusininae (Gastropoda, Fasciolariidae). Basteria, 82 (4 - 6), 57 - 82." type="journal article" year="2018">Vermeij &amp; Snyder (2018)</bibRefCitation>
introduced ten more genera to bring more precise organization to many of the larger species that still remained in 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyons &amp; Snyder, 2019" authorityName="Lyons &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2019" box="[495,584,1124,1147]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" sensu="lato" status="s.l.">
<emphasis box="[495,584,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Fusinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[595,627,1122,1147]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[595,620,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">s.l</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
However, although Vermeij &amp; Snyder assigned many species among 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyons &amp; Snyder, 2019" authorityName="Lyons &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2019" box="[151,240,1159,1182]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" sensu="stricto" status="s.s.">
<emphasis box="[151,240,1159,1182]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Fusinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[248,284,1159,1182]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[248,276,1159,1182]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">s.s</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and their genera, many other speciess were not dealt with and must remain in 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyons &amp; Snyder, 2019" authorityName="Lyons &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2019" box="[1186,1275,1159,1182]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" sensu="lato" status="s.l.">
<emphasis box="[1186,1275,1159,1182]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Fusinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1284,1316,1158,1183]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[1284,1309,1158,1183]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">s.l</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
until such time that this is done. Three Guianan species formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lyons &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2019" box="[876,965,1196,1219]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[876,965,1196,1219]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Fusinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were reclassified by Vermeij &amp; Snyder in their new genera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vermeij &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2018" box="[358,490,1231,1255]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Lyonsifusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[358,490,1231,1255]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Lyonsifusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[553,686,1231,1255]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vermeij &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2018" box="[553,683,1231,1255]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Aristofusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Aristofusus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
We retain other Guianan species not reclassified by Vermeij &amp; Snyder in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyons &amp; Snyder, 2019" authorityName="Lyons &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2019" box="[379,468,1268,1291]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" sensu="lato" status="s.l.">
<emphasis box="[379,468,1268,1291]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Fusinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[475,508,1266,1291]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[475,501,1266,1291]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">s.l</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="244" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,978,1399]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">
Two other new genera of Vermeij and Snyder containing species mentioned in the following accounts are 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vermeij &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,279,1339,1363]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Africofusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,279,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Africofusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[298,348,1339,1363]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Lamarck, 1816" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1816" box="[452,812,1338,1363]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ocellifer">
<emphasis box="[452,624,1338,1363]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Fusus ocellifer</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lamarck, J. B. P. A. de" box="[636,812,1338,1363]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" pagination="391 - 488" refId="ref27408" refString="Lamarck, J. B. P. A. de M. (1816) Tableau Encyclopedique et Methodique des Trois Regnes de la Nature. Vingt-Troisieme Partie. Mollusques et Polypes Divers. Liste des Objets Representes dans les Planches se Cette Livraison. Mme. Veuve Agasse, Imprimeur-Libraire, Paris, 16 pp., pls. 391 - 488, 431 bis, 431 bis *." type="book chapter" year="1816">Lamarck, 1816</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vermeij &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2018" box="[884,1011,1339,1363]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Goniofusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[884,1011,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Goniofusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1031,1081,1339,1363]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Kiener, 1840" authorityName="Kiener" authorityYear="1840" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="dupetitthouarsi">
<emphasis box="[1186,1436,1338,1363]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Fusus dupetitthouarsi</emphasis>
Kiener, 1840
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
